SUB_1: I'll enumerate promising Steiner trees connecting Port, Pine, Rock.

Interference pairs (edges in conflict graph): Bay-Port, Bay-Cliff, Bay-Dune, Cliff-Port, Cliff-Pine, Dune-Port, Cape-Cliff, Cape-Pine.

Candidate 1 (baseline): Port-Rock(22), Dune-Port(7), Dune-Pine(25). Active: Port,Rock,Dune,Pine. Conflicts among active: Bay-Port(Bay inactive), Dune-Port(active!). So Dune≠Port. Pine,Rock free. Colors: Port=1,Dune=2,Pine=1,Rock=1. 2 colors. Cost=54+30=84.

Candidate 2: Bay-Port(2), Bay-Rock(22), Cape-Pine(8), Cape-Rock(17). Tree? Bay-Port, Bay-Rock, Cape-Rock, Cape-Pine. Check: Bay connects Port,Rock; Cape connects Rock,Pine via Cape-Rock. Is this a tree on {Port,Bay,Rock,Cape,Pine}? Edges: Bay-Port, Bay-Rock, Cape-Rock, Cape-Pine = 4 edges, 5 nodes. Yes, tree. Cable cost=2+22+17+8=49. Active: Port,Bay,Rock,Cape,Pine. Conflicts: Bay-Port(active,active)→Bay≠Port; Cape-Pine(active,active)→Cape≠Pine; Bay-Dune(Dune inactive); Cliff-Pine(Cliff inactive); Cape-Cliff(Cliff inactive). So constraints: Bay≠Port, Cape≠Pine. Assign: Port=1,Bay=2,Rock=1,Cape=1,Pine=2. Check: Bay≠Port(2≠1✓), Cape≠Pine(1≠2✓). 2 colors. Total=49+30=79. Better than 84!

Candidate 3: Bay-Port(2), Dune-Mill(3), Bay-Dune(7), Cape-Pine(8), Cape-Rock(17). Tree on {Port,Bay,Dune,Mill,Cape,Pine,Rock}? Edges: Bay-Port, Bay-Dune, Dune-Mill, Cape-Pine, Cape-Rock. 5 edges, 6 nodes... wait 7 nodes need 6 edges. Missing connection between {Bay,Dune,Mill,Port} and {Cape,Pine,Rock}. Need one more edge. Add Cape-Mill(22)? Cost=2+3+7+8+17+22=59. 6 edges, 7 nodes. Tree. Active conflicts: Bay-Port(✓), Bay-Dune(✓), Dune-Port(Port-Bay-Dune path, Dune-Port not an edge but both active→Dune≠Port), Cape-Pine(✓). Assign: Port=1, Bay=2(≠Port), Dune=1(≠Bay), Mill=1, Cape=1, Pine=2(≠Cape), Rock=1. Check Dune-Port: Dune=1,Port=1 → CONFLICT! Dune≠Port required. Fix: Dune=2. Then Bay=2,Dune=2→no constraint between Bay-Dune... wait Bay-Dune IS an interference pair! Bay=2,Dune=2→CONFLICT. Need 3 colors. Cost=59+45=104. Worse.

Candidate 2 looks best at 79. Let me verify: edges Bay-Port, Bay-Rock, Cape-Rock, Cape-Pine. Connected? Bay-Port(yes), Bay-Rock(yes), Cape-Rock(yes, connects Cape to Bay component), Cape-Pine(yes). All of Port,Pine,Rock included. Tree with no cycles (5 nodes, 4 edges, connected). Valid!

